{{\b
Aims of the course: }}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{A good knowledge of the office pack is useful for students both for 
elaboration of seminar papers, bachelor and master thesis and in everyday 
business\'2e This course focuses on advanced functions of office software 
\uc1\u8211? data analysis spread sheets, programmes for text elaboration, 
presentation and for creating, recording, categorizing and searching 
information\'2e With respect to the equipment of classrooms at the 
University of Economics in Prague, Microsoft Excel, Microsoft Word, 
Microsoft PowerPoint, Microsoft OneNote and Adobe Acrobat are used 
in this course\'2e Successful completion of this course can be a good 
starting point for passing tests in 3 modules (3, 4, 6) of the international 
certificate ECDL\'2e ECDL testing is available (a fee is charged) 
at many testing centres in the Czech Republic\'2e In general, knowledge 
of 7 modules is tested (1\'2e Concepts of ICT, 2\'2e Using the computer 
and managing files, 3\'2e Word processing, 4\'2e Spread sheets, 5\'2e 
Using databases, 6\'2e Graphic facilities of PC and ways of electronic 
presentation, 7\'2e Services of information network)\'2e The ECDL 
certificate is common in the EU countries, where it is widely used 
and required especially in the state administration\'2e Known as ICDL, 
it is also popular outside Europe\'2e \line
}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
\pard\intbl\ql
{\~}\cell\row\pard
}{\trowd\trleft0\trgaph60
\clvertalt\cellx9430
